annotationA: Translation initiation factor activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: translational initiation
annotationB: Density-regulated protein homolog; Regulates translation as part of a complex with MCTS1. Specifically required for translational re-initiation in mRNAs containing upstream open reading frames (uORFs). Not required for standard translational initiation. Regulates expression of a subset of gene products including mbc, InR and EcR
